HashMap Internals (L5 Level)

              We'll go much deeper into HashMap later, but for now understand the basics.

A HashMap works like this:

                          Key
                          
                          ↓
                          
                          hashCode()
                          
                          ↓
                          
                          Hash Function
                          
                          ↓
                          
                          Bucket
                          
                          ↓
                          
                          Store Entry

    When you call:    map.put(7, 1);
    
    The JVM:    
          Computes the hash code for 7.
          Maps that hash to a bucket.
          Stores the key-value pair there.
    
    When you call:    map.get(7);

              It performs the same calculation to find the bucket quickly.

              This is why average lookup is O(1).
